Blade and Hide armor and weapons
This is a decent set of armor, made to be worn my humans or half-elves. From the looks of it, it wouldn't fit any other race without cutting or stretching.
This is an unusual set of leather armor, made to be worn by dwarves. From the looks of it, it wouldn't fit any other race without cutting or stretching.
This is an unusual set of studded leathers, made to be worn by dwarves.
The light build of this padded armour means that, with relative ease, it can be re-fitted by a tanner or clothier for use by members of any humanoid race.
This is a warm wool cloak
This is a pipe carved out of wood and bone.
This is a broom... nothing more,  nothing less.
This is a flute.  It is by no means low-quality, but it is nothing special, either.
This hoe is used for tilling soil.
This lotion, made from various plant and animal products, is applied to the skin for a smooth, pleasant-scented feel.
This is a standard lantern, you must refill it with oil every 6 hours of use.
This is an oil flask.  You may use it to refill a lantern, or try to light it and throw at someone
These bandages may be used to provide first aid or long-term care.  They do not treat poison or disease.
